</md></sn><sn><md>## D Type Climate in K√∂ppen Climate Classification

The **D type climate** in K√∂ppen‚Äôs classification is called the **Snow Climate** or **Microthermal Climate**. It is typically found in the interiors and high latitudes of continents, mainly in the Northern Hemisphere. These climates are characterized by **cold winters, short summers, and a large annual range of temperature**.

### Characteristics of D Type Climate

* Found only in the **Northern Hemisphere** (between 40¬∞‚Äì70¬∞ N).
* Experiences **severe winters** with average temperature of the coldest month **below ‚Äì3¬∞C**.
* Warmest month has an average temperature **above 10¬∞C**.
* Annual temperature range is very high (continental effect).
* Precipitation is moderate and can occur throughout the year or seasonally, often in the form of **snow during winter**.
* Vegetation: Coniferous forests (Taiga) are typical.

